<TITLE> Bashundhara boss faces two cases </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, May 13 (bdnews24.com)  Two cases have been filed against Bashundhara Group Ahmed Akbar Sobhan, also known as Shah Alam, accusing him of trespassing on government property, cutting away earth and threatening government officers. The cases also charged another 40-50 unidentified people. Officer in charge of Kaliakair Police Station Mohammed Amir Hossain confirmed bdnews24.com about the cases, filed on Thursday by Shafipur union's assistant land officer Mohammed Mokhlesur Rahman. Sub-inspector Mohammed Chan Mia of Kaliakair police told bdnews24.com that the cases were filed around 8pm under section 447, 379, 189 and 109 of the CrPC. According to the cases, on Apr 28, 40-50 Bashundhara Group workers, on orders of their chairman, entered the government property at Madhyaparha Mouja and dug away earth for land-filling their Bashundhara-Mouchak City Housing project. Officials of the union's land office were threatened with dire consequences when they had tried to stop Bashundhara men, the cases said. The next day, another 30-35 Bashundhara workers cut away earth from another government property in a similar manner. Bashundhara group officials could not be contacted on phone. bdnews
